 1 portion","carbohydrates":"10.3 g","calories":"1310 kJ \/ 312 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, large bowl, serving bowls","hintsAndTricks":["You can find black fungus at most Asian food stores. Alternatively, you can use fresh or dried wood ear mushrooms for this recipe (if using fresh, omit the soaking time).","Black vinegar is a dark Chinese vinegar with a woody, smoky flavour. Some versions are rice-based, while others are wheat-based. Chinese rice wine (also known as Shaoxing wine) is a common Chinese cooking wine. Both are available at Asian food stores.","Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","55m","4 portion"]}